title: Bug 121170: IMetaData.getColumnLabel() returns different results before/after data extraction
OB: When calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction, the method does not return user recognizable strings.
EB: IMetaData.getColumnLabel() should return user recognizable strings both before and after data extraction.
SR:
To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction.
2. Note the result.
3. Perform data extraction.
4. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() again.
5. Compare the result before and after data extraction.
